    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dip the<strong> butterflied chicken</strong> in the<strong> milk</strong>, then coat with the<strong> Nashville-style</strong> <strong>chicken coating</strong> until both sides are well coated</p><p>Add the<strong> coated</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) lined with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Nashville-style hot free range chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
